column5: I have all the windows and front door open.  What a beauty of a day to being doing chores and smoking some meat.  I should be fishing. LOL
Just got back from my daily 4 mile hike Brian and was over dressed with just a light polyester T-shirt and jacket. Spent yesterday afternoon washing the truck in the driveway.

I went to SanFrancisco fish market. Think about it Brian! How do you tell and old Italian lady,Â if I can call her that, that the mussels are alive when they are closed, the owner was almost going to give up!!!!! Merry Christmas to all.
58 degrees and light south winds here, a 13.76 walleye caught over the weekend, the fall brawl may have ended, but the walleye fishing hasn't.
What am I to think about ?  If it,s closed,there's no business happening . Thinkaboutit Albert . HAHAHA
Wall to wall Italians Brian! they did have a jar of caviar and focaccia with an olive oil dip for the people in line!
Starskys had a fresh fish booth. Lined up they were. All for some carp.LOL
